Document: AABB
Path: godot/classes/class_aabb.rst
Summary: Operator methods for comparing and transforming AABB objects.

Method: operator !=(AABB right) → bool
Returns true if the position or size of both bounding boxes are not equal. Note: Due to floating-point precision errors, consider using is_equal_approx() instead, which is more reliable.

Method: operator *(Transform3D right) → AABB
Inversely transforms (multiplies) the AABB by the given Transform3D transformation matrix, assuming the transformation basis is orthonormal (rotation/reflection allowed, scaling/skew not allowed). The operation "aabb * transform" is equivalent to "transform.inverse() * aabb". For affine transformations with scaling, use "transform.affine_inverse() * aabb" instead.

Method: operator ==(AABB right) → bool
Returns true if both position and size of the bounding boxes are exactly equal. Note: Due to floating-point precision errors, consider using is_equal_approx() instead, which is more reliable.